  "texts": [
    "Therefore, when historical data properties in a time series remain constant in the future, the forecasting model tends to be reliable and yield good results.",
    "Conversely, if the time series is nonstationary, forecasting the future from statistical properties obtained directly from historical data may carry the risk of unreliability 26, 27.",
    "Therefore, the ADF test, a common test method for time series stationarity, is used in this paper.",
    "Since the experiment divided the yearly data into four seasons for forecasting, the data from each season needed to be tested separately (Table 1).",
    ":(0123456789) Scientific Reports | (2024) 14:6744 | https://doi.org/10.1038/s41598-024-56751-6"
  ]
}